SIMPLE: eliminate
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Eliminate
<hw>E*lim"i*nate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp.
& p. p.</pos> <conjf>Eliminated</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Eliminating</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>.]</vmorph> <ety>[L.
<ets>eliminatus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>eliminare</ets>; <ets>e</ets> out +
<ets>limen</ets> threshold; prob. akin to <ets>limes</ets> boundary. See
<er>Limit</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>To put out of doors; to expel;
to discharge; to release; to set at liberty.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Eliminate</qex> my spirit, give it range⟦br⟧
Through provinces of thought yet unexplored.</q>
<rj><qau>Young.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Alg.)</fld> <def>To cause to disappear from an
equation; <as>as, to <ex>eliminate</ex> an unknown
quantity</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>To set aside as unimportant in a process of
inductive inquiry; to leave out of consideration.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Eliminate</qex> errors that have been gathering and
accumulating.</q> <rj><qau>Lowth.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <def>To obtain by separating, as from foreign matters; to
deduce; <as>as, to <ex>eliminate</ex> an idea or a
conclusion</as>.</def> <mark>[Recent, and not well
authorized]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>5.</sn> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>To separate; to expel from the
system; to excrete; <as>as, the kidneys <ex>eliminate</ex> urea, the
lungs carbonic acid; to <ex>eliminate</ex> poison from the
system.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Elimination</ent>⟦br⟧
